                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G 1A/216</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Caffery</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-02">October 2,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I had a visit this afternoon from Señor Dr. Don Fernando González Roa, Mexican
                    Ambassador, who came to tell me that he had received instructions from his
                    Government to inform us that Dr. Puig had given up his idea of having the
                    proposed additions to the agenda for the Montevideo Conference approved by the
                    Pan American Union. Dr. Puig had told him to convey the same information to Dr.
                        Rowe.<note n="26" xml:id="d23fn26">Leo S. Rowe, Director General, Pan
                        American Union.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">efferson</hi>] C[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >affery</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
